# Router-on-a-Stick (ROAS) Lab

## Objective
Configure Router-on-a-Stick (ROAS) with 3 VLANs on a switch.  
DHCP will be configured on the router.  
All VLANs must receive IP addresses and successfully ping a server in a different network.


## Requirements
- 2 × Cisco L3 IOU
- 1 × Cisco L2 IOU
- 3 × VPC
- 1 × Tiny Linux Server

## What You Will Do
- Create 3 VLANs on the switch  
- Configure trunk between switch and router  
- Configure ROAS (subinterfaces on router)  
- Configure DHCP on router  
- Verify IP assignment for all VLANs  
- Test connectivity to server network  

## Expected Outcome
- All VPCs receive correct IP via DHCP  
- All VLANs can successfully ping the server  

## Lab Files
- IOU images are available in the provided Google Drive link  
- Follow the setup guide to import images into PNETLab  
- Import the `.unl` file into PNETLab to access the solution lab  

## Note
A complete working solution is available in the lab files for reference.
